correctness.rationale: Several core fields are accurate (SALD method for ZnO; T=200 °C; GPC ~1.7 Å/cycle; 176 cycles; ~300 nm film; mobility 16.7 cm^2/V·s; n≈1.99; AFM roughness 17.3 nm), but the extraction contains multiple schema violations, incorrect values, and unsupported entries. Key issues: (1) Schema violations: plasmaPower, supercycleDesign set to None though type requires object (optional fields should be omitted, not set to null); nucleationPeriod, dosingTime, purgeTime, conformality.aspectRatio, filmComposition.elementalConcentration.values.quantityValue.numericValue, filmDensity.value.quantityValue.numericValue contain nulls where numbers are required. (2) Incorrect/unsupported parameters: pressure set to 220 mTorr—this is TMA partial pressure for Al2O3, not ZnO reactor pressure; SALD operates in open air and ZnO channel partial pressures are DEZ 310 mTorr, H2O 170 mTorr, NH3 ~6 Torr. flowRates misuse sccm units to represent partial pressures (310, 170) and thus are not traceable; saturation set to True without support for ZnO (only Al2O3 saturation behavior discussed); uniformity variation reported as 50%—the article reports threshold voltage variation <50 mV (device-level), not thickness uniformity; device thresholdVoltage is given as 2.9 V, which is the turn-on voltage—article states extracted threshold ≈2.0 V. (3) Missing/placeholder values: carrierGas and purgingGas set to “Not Found” (not traceable); substrate set to “Not Found” despite ZnO being deposited on an Al2O3 dielectric on Cr-coated glass for the TFTs; dosing/purge times should use the reported 63 ms residence time per channel instead of nulls; ammonia used as N-dopant in the water stream is omitted from reactant details. (4) Process coverage: The article also reports a distinct ZnO deposition for selective area studies (DEZ 100 mTorr, H2O 35 mTorr, 600 cycles, ~980 nm), which is not extracted as a separate process. Corrections needed: remove null-typed optional objects; replace null numerics with article-supported values (e.g., 63 ms for dosing/purge); fix pressure and flow fields to reflect reported partial pressures (or leave flow rates absent if not provided); set saturation to supported value; correct uniformity and threshold voltage; provide substrate and gases from the text or leave out if schema allows; add the second ZnO process if required by the task.

completeness.rationale: Significant incompleteness and schema violations. Key issues: (1) Multiple processes missing: article reports at least two distinct ZnO S‑ALD conditions—TFT ZnO (DEZ 310 mTorr; H2O 170 mTorr; ~6 Torr NH3; 63 ms; 176 cycles; ~300 Å film) and patterning study ZnO (DEZ 100 mTorr; H2O 35 mTorr; 63 ms; 600 cycles; ~980 Å)—but only one process is extracted; refractive index (n≈1.99 at 700 nm) was taken from the patterning run yet attached to the TFT process. (2) Unit/value errors: filmThickness recorded as 300 nm instead of ~300 Å (~30 nm) for the 176-cycle TFT ZnO; growth-per-cycle 1.7 Å × 176 cycles ≈ 299 Å contradicts 300 nm entry. (3) Misassigned parameters: pressure set to 220 mTorr (actually a TMA partial pressure for Al2O3, not ZnO reactor pressure; S‑ALD operated in open air ≈ 760 Torr); flowRates field misused with partial pressures (310 and 170 mTorr) and sccm units, violating schema semantics. (4) Missing/incorrect chemistry: co-reactant should include H2O with NH3 (ammonia present as dopant in water stream ~6 Torr); substrate for ZnO should be Al2O3 dielectric on Cr/glass, not “Not Found.” (5) Device parameters: thresholdVoltage entered as 2.9 V (this is turn-on voltage; threshold from linear fit ≈ 2.0 V). (6) Uniformity: filled as 50% by misreading 50 mV threshold variation; schema expects thickness uniformity—no such data provided. (7) Saturation flag set True for ZnO without textual support (saturation discussion and value pertain to Al2O3). (8) Numerous schema violations via nulls/placeholder strings: many required numeric fields are None (e.g., dosingTime, purgeTime, conformality.aspectRatio, filmComposition.elementalConcentration, filmDensity), and optional objects provided as None (plasmaPower, supercycleDesign), which breaks type constraints and the “no null” requirement. (9) Unsupported composition: atomicRatio ‘Zn:O = 1:1’ and elemental concentrations lack source characterization (no XPS/EDS/RBS reported). To improve: add a second ZnO process for the patterning run; correct film thickness units; set substrate to Al2O3/Cr/glass; represent open-air pressure properly; move partial pressures to an appropriate field (not flowRates) and include NH3; populate dosing/purge times with the reported 63 ms; fix threshold voltage to ~2.0 V; remove or correctly populate uniformity and composition fields; omit optional objects instead of setting None; ensure all numeric fields have valid values with QUDT-compliant units.
